          "datePublished": "2014-12-11",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "lovely school. been here since nursery.  The best teachers teach us over here. This school helps you to focus on wat u r good at. spent months trying to get admission in other schools but this school gave me admission in 1 day. best thing about the school is that each class unlike most of the other schools had only 20-25 students in each class and the teachers give everyone their attention. This school is full of artists and sportsmen. joining this school is the best thing u can do. so please join",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Calcutta International School - Sreepally,Bhowanipore"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Saha Biswas"
          },
          "datePublished": "2014-07-04",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "My experience with Calcutta International School was pathetic. I went 5 times to the school and waited 3 months to get administrator for the interview for my daughter's admission. During interview I faced bunch of stupid questions from bunch of shameless middle-aged women administrators and finally they declined to admit my daughter for a non-sense reason. They declined the right of basic education of a child. The day they declined, I went to South City International School and my daughter got admitted in the same day in 2 hours. My daughter studied 2 years in South City and now we are back to USA.\n\nI felt humiliated as if I am a second class citizen in India. I felt that the school is just like a super-slow bureaucrat government department, only difference is that the building walls are clean in one case and dirty in other.\n\nThe school board is greedy. The amount of admission money they asked is ridiculous and shows that the school is interested only in profit making business.\n\nFinally I thank God that my daughter did not get admitted in Calcutta International School. In South City, she got great atmosphere, great teachers, great administration and extraordinary curriculum.\n\nI sincerely suggest do not admit your children in Calcutta International School.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        }
